
Overview of noun salvage

The noun salvage has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                      
1. salvage -- (property or goods saved from damage or destruction)
2. salvage -- (the act of saving goods or property that were in danger of damage or destruction)
3. salvage -- (the act of rescuing a ship or its crew or its cargo from a shipwreck or a fire)

Overview of verb salvage

The verb salvage has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (3) salvage, salve, relieve, save -- (save from ruin, destruction, or harm)
2. salvage, scavenge -- (collect discarded or refused material; "She scavenged the garbage cans for food")
